The subclass is calling a public method, but how the called method works, ie., what private fields or methods it accesses, is not the calling method&#39;s business. The subclass itself is not directly calling the private method, so there is no problem.  
This is also how getters and setters work...

    private String name;
    public void setName(String name){
      //do something
      this.name=name;
    }
    public String getName(){
      //do something
      return name;
    }

If methods from other classes could not call the getters and setters, they would have no reason to exist.  
In fact, if you think about it, **if public methods could not be called because somewhere in the chain of execution a private field or method is accessed, then private fields or methods would not be used anywhere other than the main class.**

