You need to specify the parameter with the right syntax:

    mvn checkstyle:check -Dincludes=&quot;src/main/java/MyClass.java&quot;

For further information: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-checkstyle-plugin/check-mojo.html

The path should be relative to your [source directory][1].

This uniquely identifies the single file `src/main/java/MyClass.java` as it doesn&#39;t use a wildcard path.

    mvn checkstyle:check -Dcheckstyle.includes=&quot;MyClass.java&quot;


More typically you would be using java packages to namespace your classes.

    mvn checkstyle:check -Dcheckstyle.includes=&quot;com/example/myapp/MyClass.java&quot;

  [1]: https://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-checkstyle-plugin/check-mojo.html#sourceDirectories

You can use hooks (see https://www.baeldung.com/java-cucumber-hooks)

```java
